<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> There are numerous instances of opposition leadership saying they're not interested in safe or clean nuclear power.<br>
They sabotage every step towards making it safer &amp; cleaner, just because it makes nuclear power less tenable. (If they were just honest enough, every time they spout about how unsafe and uneconomical (they imagine) it is, to remind the listener that they made it that way, I might not see them as the back-stabbing liars they are)<br>
With sane regulation and management, it could be as safe and clean as anything else we could devise. Without the sabotage of the anti-nuclear movement, we could today have zero problems with contamination &amp; pollution from nuclear power. &quot;Waste&quot; wouldn't be. We mightn't be burning coal today, the world mightn't be as heavily dependant on mid-east oil. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
